{{nihongo|'''Kikujirō Fukushima'''|福島 菊次郎|Fukushima Kikujirō|March 15, 1921 &ndash; September 24, 2015}} was a Japanese [[photographer]],<ref>{{ja icon}} Tokyo Metropolitan Museum of Photography, editor. {{nihongo|''328 Outstanding Japanese Photographers''|『日本写真家事典』|''Nihon shashinka jiten}}. Kyoto: Tankōsha, 2000. {{ISBN|4-473-01750-8}}</ref> author of the book ''Postwar Japan that was not photographed: From Hiroshima to Fukushima''.
== Film == The [[documentary film]] ''Nippon no Uso'' (''Japan Lies—The Photojournalism of Kikujiro Fukushima, Age 90'') provides insight into the life of Fukushima. Based on Fukushima’s 250,000 photos and his own experiences, the film shows the little-known side of Japan’s [[Postwar Japan|postwar]] path. Directed by Saburo Hasegawa and produced by Documentary Japan, the film was released on August 4, 2012 in Tokyo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/appendix/feature/Kikujiro_Special.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120810105440/http://ajw.asahi.com/appendix/feature/Kikujiro_Special.html |archivedate=2012-08-10 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/text/ff20120803a1.html|title='Nippon no Uso: Hodo Shashinka Fukushima Kikujiro 90-sai (Japan Lies)' - The Japan Times|work=The Japan Times|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://japandailypress.com/japan-lies-documentary-about-photojournalist-kikujiro-fukushima-reaps-awards-1323241/|title=‘Japan Lies’ documentary about photojournalist Kikujiro Fukushima reaps awards - The Japan Daily Press|work=japandailypress.com|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>
== Death == He died after a [[stroke]] on September 24, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mainichi.jp/english/english/newsselect/news/20150925p2a00m0na014000c.html|title=Renowned photojournalist Kikujiro Fukushima dies at 94|work=mainichi.jp|accessdate=25 September 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925173010/http://mainichi.jp/english/english/newsselect/news/20150925p2a00m0na014000c.html|archivedate=25 September 2015|df=}}</ref>
