vernment issues an official conclusion as to the cause of Minamata disease and Niigata Minamata disease |- | align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| <big>'''1969'''</big> | bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| |- | align="center" valign="top" | 14 June || Litiagtion Group of the Mutual Aid Society files a lawsuit against Chisso in the Kumamoto District Court |- | align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| <big>'''1970'''</big> | bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| |- | align="center" valign="top" | 4 July || [[Hajime Hosokawa]] testifies from his deathbed about his cat experiments in the Litigation Group trial |- | align="center" valign="top" | 27 May || Arbitrated compensation agreement between Chisso and the Arbitration Group of the Mutual Aid Society |- | align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| <big>'''1971'''</big> | bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| |- | align="center" valign="top" | 29 September || Showa Denko found guilty of [[negligence]]; Niigata patients win compensation |- | align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| <big>'''1972'''</big> | bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| |- | align="center" valign="top" bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| <big>'''1973'''</big> | bgcolor="#C0C0C0"| |- | align="center" valign="top" | 20 March || Chisso found guilty of [[negligence]]; Litigation Group patients win compensation |- | align="center" valign="top" | 1977 || A net is installed around Minamata Bay to prevent toxic sludge and fish from contaminating other areas |- | align="center" valign="top" | 1 September 1997 || The net surrounding Minamata Bay is removed and fish caught there are declared safe to eat |- | align="center" valign="top" | 15 October 2004 || The [[Supreme Court of Japan]] rules that the national government was responsible for not preventing the spread of Minamata disease after 1960 |- | align="center" valign="top" | || |- | align="center" valign="top" | || |} <!-- Note: References etc. have been copied directly from [[Minamata disease]]. They have not actually been used in this article. -->
