'''Timothy S. George''' is a Professor of History and Chair of the [[University of Rhode Island]] Department of History. He specializes in Postwar Japanese history,Citizen-corporation-state relations in Japan from Meiji through Shōwa, local history, and environmental history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Timothy S. George|url= http://www.uri.edu/artsci/his/george.html|publisher=University of Rhode Island|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref> A [[Fulbright Scholar]], George's research has been reviewed in ''Environmental History'',<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=3985458|title=Review of Minamata: Pollution and the Struggle for Democracy in Postwar Japan|first=Kazuto|last=Oshio|date=1 January 2002|publisher=|journal=Environmental History|volume=7|issue=1|pages=126–127|doi=10.2307/3985458}}</ref> ''[[The Journal of Asian Studies]]'',<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=2700238|title=Review of Minamata: Pollution and the Struggle for Democracy in Postwar Japan|first=Karen|last=Colligan-Taylor|date=1 January 2002|publisher=|journal=The Journal of Asian Studies|volume=61|issue=1|pages=251–253|doi=10.2307/2700238}}</ref> ''[[Social Science Japan Journal]]'',<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=30209389|title=Review of Minamata: Pollution and the Struggle for Democracy in Postwar Japan|first=Anja|last=Osiander|date=1 January 2002|publisher=|journal=Social Science Japan Journal|volume=5|issue=2|pages=273–275}}</ref> and the ''[[Journal of Japanese Studies]]''.<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=25064377|title=Review of Minamata: Pollution and the Struggle for Democracy in Postwar Japan|first=Miranda A.|last=Schreurs|date=1 January 2003|publisher=|journal=Journal of Japanese Studies|volume=29|issue=1|pages=153–156}}</ref> He is a Faculty Affiliate of Harvard University's Program on U.S.-Japan Relations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Timothy S. George|url= http://programs.wcfia.harvard.edu/us-japan/people/timothy-s-george|publisher=   The President and Fellows of Harvard College|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>

==Education and background==
George graduated [[Stanford University]] A. B. in 1977, the [[University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa]] with his M.A. in 1984, and then attended [[Harvard University]], where he earned his A.M. in 1993 and his Ph.D. in 1996.<ref>{{cite web|title=Timothy S. George|url= http://www.uri.edu/artsci/his/george.html|publisher=University of Rhode Island|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>

==Selected honors and awards==
*2008-2009: Winner of the [[URI Center for the Humanities]] Faculty Research Grant.<ref>{{cite web|title=Recent Grant and Fellowship Awards|url= http://web.uri.edu/humanities/recents/|publisher=University of Rhode Island|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>
*2013: Winner of the U.S. Fulbright Scholarship to study at the [[University of Tokyo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Timothy George|url= http://www.cies.org/grantee/timothy-george|publisher=Council for International Exchange of Scholars|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>

